(32,'Sweepatic','employee16@howest.be','499998519','Kapeldreef 60','3001','Leuven','www.sweepatic.com','Sweepatic is a young innovative cybersecurity company operating on a global scale making our customers more cyber resilient. \n\nOur innovative cloud platform maps, monitors and manages attack surfaces across the world producing high impact insights and easy-to-remediate findings. \n\nTo learn more about Sweepatic, visit https://www.sweepatic.com and follow Sweepatic on social media (LinkedIn, Facebook, Twitter and Insta)','Jr. Security Analyst (\"hunter\") internship:\n\nPhase 1 of internship) Main focus is the monitoring of customer scopes on the Sweepatic attack surface management platform. This includes, but is not limited to the triage, assigning of tags and preparing of small tactical \"hunting\" activity, producing fact-based reports detailing the observations in a clear, professional way to customer users.\n\nRelease testing: hunt for application bugs or other problems with the product, prior to production release.\n\nPerform an external security test (including vulnerability scan) covering the network, infrastructure, and application layer of the Sweepatic systems and applications related to the product. Presentation of the findings to the internal team.\n\nPhase 2 of the internship) \n\nSupport the Sweepatic product manager in conducting light research on current ongoing reconnaissance and/or OSINT trends, security testing standards as needed with a goal of reporting noticed threats applicable to our customers and developing feature requests (via small proof of concept) on how to address them (via technical specs) from a technical roadmap perspective (e.g. creation of new platform observations, dashboard information elements and/or report elements)\n\nWrite \"in-portal\" tactical documentations on existing features, to educate and increase the engagement of users within the Sweepatic platform.\n\nSweepatic day to day contacts:\n\nOverall: CEO \nPhase 1) 